cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.LG 

This paper deals with mining and predicting user interest similarity in online social networks, which involves analyzing demographic and social features of users. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses machine learning methods to combine multiple features, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with video recommendation, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper is based on a dataset from Tencent, a popular service provider in China, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SOC (Computers and Society).
